2. LICENSE GRANTS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Licensor grants the Licensee one (and only one) of the following
license types, determined by the Licensee's active Subscription and any
separately executed order form or master agreement between the parties.
Absent a valid grant under 2.1–2.5, no rights are granted in the
Enterprise Edition.

2.1 MANAGED USE LICENSE

If the Licensee holds an active Subscription to the Managed Service,
the Licensor grants the Licensee a non-exclusive, non-transferable,
non-sublicensable, worldwide right, during the Subscription term, to
use the Enterprise Edition solely via the Managed Service.

A Managed Use License does NOT grant the Licensee any right to:
 (a) download, copy, or retain the Enterprise Edition source or
     binaries;
 (b) deploy or execute the Enterprise Edition on any infrastructure
     other than the Managed Service;
 (c) use the Enterprise Edition after the Subscription ends.

2.2 ON-PREMISES DEPLOYMENT LICENSE

If and only if the parties have executed a separate written order form
or master subscription agreement explicitly granting On-Premises
Deployment rights, the Licensor grants the Licensee a non-exclusive,
non-transferable, non-sublicensable, worldwide right, during the
Subscription term, to install, execute, and operate the Enterprise
Edition on Licensee-controlled infrastructure, limited to:

 (a) the number of Instances specified in the order form;
 (b) the number of Authorized Users specified in the order form;
 (c) Production Use and/or Non-Production Use as specified in the
     order form.

If any of (a), (b), or (c) is not specified, the default is one (1)
Instance, Authorized Users capped at the Subscription tier's documented
limit, and Non-Production Use only.

2.3 EVALUATION LICENSE

The Licensor grants any individual or entity a non-exclusive,
non-transferable, non-sublicensable, worldwide right to install and
execute the Enterprise Edition for the sole purpose of internal
evaluation, subject to all of the following:

 (a) evaluation period does not exceed sixty (60) days from first use;
 (b) use is limited to one (1) Instance and a maximum of five (5)
     Authorized Users;
 (c) Non-Production Use only;
 (d) no benchmark, competitive analysis, or public performance claim
     may be published without the Licensor's prior written consent;
 (e) at the end of the evaluation period, the Licensee must either
     obtain a paid Subscription covering the Enterprise Edition or
     cease all use and destroy all copies of the Enterprise Edition.

2.4 OEM / EMBEDDED LICENSE

Any distribution, sublicensing, or embedding of the Enterprise Edition
within a product or service offered by the Licensee to third parties
REQUIRES a separately executed OEM agreement with the Licensor. This
License alone grants no OEM, embedding, or sublicensing rights. Contact
licensing@contentrain.io.

2.5 WHITE-LABEL / RESELLER LICENSE

Any rebranding of Contentrain Studio or the Enterprise Edition, removal
or replacement of Licensor trademarks, or resale of Subscriptions to
third parties REQUIRES a separately executed white-label or reseller
agreement with the Licensor. This License alone grants no white-label
or reseller rights. Contact licensing@contentrain.io.

