7. TERM AND TERMINATION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

7.1 This License is effective on the date the Licensee first downloads,
installs, accesses, or uses the Enterprise Edition and continues for
the duration of the applicable Subscription term, unless earlier
terminated.

7.2 The Licensor may terminate this License immediately upon written
notice if the Licensee materially breaches any term of this License
and fails to cure such breach within thirty (30) days after written
notice. For breaches of Section 3 (Restrictions) or Section 5
(Intellectual Property), termination is immediate and no cure period
applies.

7.3 The Licensee may terminate this License at any time by ceasing all
use of the Enterprise Edition and destroying all copies under its
control. Fees already paid are non-refundable except as expressly
provided in the applicable order form.

7.4 Upon termination or expiration of this License for any reason, the
Licensee shall, within fifteen (15) days:
 (a) cease all use of the Enterprise Edition;
 (b) uninstall and delete all copies of the Enterprise Edition from
     all Instances under the Licensee's control;
 (c) upon written request, certify such destruction in writing to the
     Licensor.

7.5 Sections 3, 4, 5, 7.4, 8, 9, 10, and 11 survive termination.

